      • findAllAnnotations

        public static <A extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> java.util.List<A> findAllAnnotations​(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                                                                                               java.lang.Class<A> annotationType)
        Finds all annotations on the given clazz. In case the annotation is not present on clazz, the super classes of clazz are also checked. This method supports repeatable annotations.
        Type Parameters:
        A - the annotation type
        Parameters:
        clazz - the class to check
        annotationType - the annotation class
        Returns:
        all found annotations, or an empty list, if the annotation is not present on any of the classes of the class hierarchy.

      • findAnnotatedFields

        public static <T extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> java.util.Map<java.lang.reflect.Field,​java.util.List<T>> findAnnotatedFields​(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                                                                                                                                             java.lang.Class<T> annotationClazz,
                                                                                                                                             boolean checkSuperClasses,
                                                                                                                                             java.util.Comparator<java.lang.reflect.Field> comparator)
        Extracts all fields annotated by annotationClazz in class clazz and returns a map, where the key is the field itself and the value is the list of annotations (which may be repeatable).
        Parameters:
        clazz - the class to be checked for annotated fields
        annotationClazz - the annotation class to be looked up for
        checkSuperClasses - flag, that determines, whether super classes shall be scanned or not
        comparator - an optional Comparator instance for sorting the resulting map
        Returns:
        a map, where the key is the field instance and the value is the list of retrieved annotations (annotations can be repeatable)

      • findAnnotatedFields

        public static <T extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation> java.util.Map<java.lang.reflect.Field,​java.util.List<T>> findAnnotatedFields​(java.lang.Class<?> clazz,
                                                                                                                                             java.lang.Class<T> annotationClazz,
                                                                                                                                             boolean checkSuperClasses)
        Extracts all fields annotated by annotationClazz in class clazz and returns a map. Because annotations may be repeatable, the value of the returned map is a list.
        Parameters:
        clazz - the class to be checked for annotated fields
        annotationClazz - the annotation class to be looked up for
        checkSuperClasses - flag, that determines, whether super classes shall be scanned or not
        Returns:
        a map, where the key is the field and the value is the list of the (repeatable) annotations.
